AGI - Premier Giorgia Meloni is participating in the Ippodromo di Tor di Quinto in Rome at the celebrations of the 163rd anniversary of the constitution of the Italian army. The President of the Council, accompanied by the Minister of Defense Guido Crosetto and the Chief of Staff of the Carmine Masiello Army, reviewed the deployments on board a tactical vehicle of the Army.
&nbsp;
"You are not asked to be heroes but to choose to be on the right side, to discern good and evil. Thousands of soldiers have done so in recent years, giving an image of Italy in the world to be proud of. You must be the presidio and defense of the country and its institutions." He underlined the Minister of Defense, Guido Crosetto, intervening at the celebration of the 163rd anniversary of the Army.
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
"In situations such as the present one, the central theme is that security is extrinsic to having an Army equipped for a range of scenarios - from conventional conflicts to new frontiers of confrontation, such as space, cyber, disinformation -, in synergy with the armed forces sisters and in harmony with the other articulations of the State and all national and international actors involved in various reasons."
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
This was said by the Chief of Staff of the Army, General Carmine Masiello, intervening at the celebration of the 163th anniversary of the constitution of the Corps. "It is necessary, therefore, a real cultural change in the whole field - Masiello has emphasized - in which innovation becomes the vital activity of the Army. But if technology can come anywhere, it's in the human resource, but it's true value. We must continue to look with affection to our soldiers, taking care of them and their families, preparing them for the worst moments. The values are the essence of our duty, to offer without prejudice, differences and compromises, always in name and for the affirmation of the fundamental goods of peace, justice and freedom," he concluded.
&nbsp;

